Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.33,0:00:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost Conan's tenth anniversary!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.12,0:00:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Overcoming one obstacle, and aiming for the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.23,0:00:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amidst the feelings of love and kindness...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.72,0:00:08.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We continue to look further into this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.17,0:00:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To find the true culprit of the mythical village!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.97,0:00:11.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:15.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.63,0:01:54.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}We traveled the old, mythical village of Izumo...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.74,0:01:59.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Where we met Ezumi Eiko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},\Na young woman working at the Grand Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.04,0:01:59.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ezumi Eiko (25)\N{\fs12} Sunrise Shop - Eldest Daughterd
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.13,0:02:04.27,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}Inome Cave
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.41,0:02:01.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The following day...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.99,0:02:04.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Eiko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s fianc√© was found dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.91,0:02:08.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And a katana worth 10 million yen was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:13.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Later, the police called four suspects to the police station...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.67,0:02:16.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And Eiko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} and her childhood friend were among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.67,0:02:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell me where you were and\Nwhat you were doing yesterday at 1:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.79,0:02:27.25,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,350)}Fukuma Ryousuke (25)\N{\fs12} Museum Curator
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.26,0:02:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had the day off yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.89,0:02:28.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I went to the former Grand Shrine station.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.77,0:02:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you, Ezumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.27,0:02:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to Hinomisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.19,0:02:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} aren't the culprits, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.90,0:02:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.07,0:02:42.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But no how we look at it, no one had a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.28,0:02:44.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That means someone is probably lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.45,0:02:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sword of the Eight-Headed Serpent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.16,0:02:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:57.03,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300}Former Grand Shrine Station
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you're not mistaking her for someone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.67,0:02:56.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I have mistaken her?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.96,0:02:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've known her since the day she was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.92,0:03:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That cute little Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} from Hinode.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.93,0:03:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw her here yesterday afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:06.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was 1:00 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.68,0:03:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she was sitting in that seat over there, as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.06,0:03:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was here\Nat the time of Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.44,0:03:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because we found a witness...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.90,0:03:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has the perfect alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.18,0:03:22.35,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ezumi= Hinomisaki
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.36,0:03:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wonder why she said she went to Hinomisaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.11,0:03:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's just inform Uncle and the others for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.34,0:03:28.89,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shimane Prefecture: Izumo Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's exactly like Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the other girl said...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.45,0:03:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was actually at the former Grand Shrine station.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.54,0:03:37.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I go there whenever I have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.63,0:03:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that's the one place I can truly relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.63,0:03:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's where my mother and father first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.01,0:03:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mother often visited Izumo on a whim...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.81,0:03:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And happened to stay at my father's inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.56,0:03:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were both charmed by the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.19,0:03:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they tied their knot of love,\Nand eventually gave birth to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.69,0:04:00.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the station is closed down now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.49,0:04:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I go there, I feel like I can see\Nthe beginning of their lives together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.49,0:04:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like that station.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.74,0:04:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why we couldn't find a witness at\NHinomisaki no matter how hard we looked, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.37,0:04:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you were never there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should've told us that you were at the\Nformer Grand Shrine station in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.92,0:04:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you lie about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.13,0:04:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.89,0:04:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said that earlier, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.43,0:04:32.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I had the day off yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:34.06,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So I went to the former Grand Shrine station.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.73,0:04:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, didn't Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nseem very surprised by his statement?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.36,0:04:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't\Nsee Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} while she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.49,0:04:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe he killed Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for my sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.78,0:04:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why I hid the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.58,0:04:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I said that I was also at the former Grand\NShrine station, it would've contradicted his testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.25,0:05:00.25,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But since I went there alone, no one can vouch for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way we wouldn't have seen\Neach other if we were at the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} lied first, giving\NEiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} no choice but to lie to cover it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.14,0:05:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hinomisaki was the first place I could think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.43,0:05:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I also like that place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.23,0:05:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.98,0:05:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if Ezumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is innocent,\Nthat casts doubt on Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.19,0:05:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, removing the katana from the\Ncrime scene to make us believe this was a robbery...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was not to cover up for Ezumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nbut cover his own tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.87,0:05:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Njust had a mutual misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.59,0:05:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mutual misunderstanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.55,0:05:50.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we tell him we stopped suspecting Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\NFukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will probably tell us the whole story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.64,0:05:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.91,0:05:55.38,Signs,,0,0,0,,Fujie-shi = Matsue Castle\NFukuma-shi = Former\NGrand Shrine Station\NIshitobi-shi = Izumo Traditional\NCultural Museum\NEzumi{\rHonorifics - Signs}-san{\r} = Hinomisa
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.64,0:05:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko, it wasn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.35,0:06:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, because I was at the former\NGrand Shrine station the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.65,0:06:07.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did I find this there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.41,0:06:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.91,0:06:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.49,0:06:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where? So...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.54,0:06:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you give us more details?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.21,0:06:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.79,0:06:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday afternoon, I actually went to Inome Cave...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.80,0:06:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't to kill Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.89,0:06:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I spoke with Eiko two days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:36.60,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You got a call from Wanibuchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.60,0:06:41.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He told me to be at Inome Cave at 1:30 PM tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.27,0:06:43.19,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why would he tell you to go to such a deserted place?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:46.94,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Whatever he's scheming can't be anything good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.94,0:06:49.74,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll go in your place...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.74,0:06:51.57,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Talk to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.57,0:06:54.16,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And get him to give up on you, Eiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:55.20,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ryo{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-chan{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.20,0:06:58.20,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tomorrow afternoon, at 1:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.29,0:07:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So yesterday, in order to have a discussion with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.29,0:07:04.50,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wanibuchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.01,0:07:13.89,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Eiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.72,0:07:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed it right away, since I'm the one who gave it to Eiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.35,0:07:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Let me hold on to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:26.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is this pendant the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.78,0:07:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought she had went there,\Neven though I told her I would.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.74,0:07:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking it was Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s doing, you decided to\Nhide the katana, masking it as a robbery-murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.04,0:07:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.21,0:07:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That certainly seems like a plausible explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry Ryo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, but I actually\Nlost this pendant a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.63,0:07:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:52.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.13,0:07:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said, the two of you\Nmisunderstood each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:07:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And each thought the other person was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.97,0:08:02.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then they lied to cover up for each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Funny, so funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.69,0:08:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not funny at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.23,0:08:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two screwed up the entire investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.82,0:08:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, removing that katana\Nwas the worst thing you could've done!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.99,0:08:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.45,0:08:22.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you hadn't picked up the pendant,\Nthe true culprit's fingerprints might have remained on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.62,0:08:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was under the wrong impression that Eiko did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:28.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.75,0:08:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't cover up a crime for the sake of love!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.88,0:08:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.18,0:08:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.39,0:08:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nmurderer is Ishitobi Kazuya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.24,0:08:46.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's true that Ishitobi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nfrightened response was strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:46.75,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Ishitobi Kazuya (35)\N{\fs10}Manager of the Izumo Soba Restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.76,0:08:52.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s surprise when you\Nfirst introduced me is bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.92,0:08:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The true culprit was carrying this pendant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.32,0:08:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the most likely scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.78,0:09:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it fell when he killed Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.66,0:09:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was placed near the corpse on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.58,0:09:09.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you lost it a few days ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.59,0:09:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you happen to meet with\NIshitobi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} around that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.09,0:09:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.13,0:09:17.30,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm begging you, Eiko{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.30,0:09:20.73,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wanibuchi will understand my situation\Nif you're the one speaking to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.74,0:09:25.22,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,350)}Fujie Takehiko (40)\N{\fs10} Manager of a Marriage Ceremony Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.30,0:09:25.96,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Marry him and talk him out of taking my company.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.48,0:09:27.52,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I beg of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.93,0:09:29.98,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are you saying, Fujie{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.61,0:09:36.45,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You want my daughter to sacrifice herself\Njust to protect your marriage ceremony hall?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.91,0:09:39.24,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm asking you to not be selfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.74,0:09:42.28,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm begging you, Eiko{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}... Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.91,0:09:44.41,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Let me think about it for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.41,0:09:47.71,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Eiko, you don't have even have to think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.71,0:09:49.96,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Go away, Fujie{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.50,0:09:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's horrible, asking you to\Nsacrifice yourself for his own personal gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.17,0:09:55.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.42,0:10:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking back now, I noticed I lost my pendant that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.43,0:10:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.47,0:10:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was at Matsue Castle and has an alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name register?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.52,0:10:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go to Matsue Castle, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.53,0:10:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit hadn't tried to frame\NEiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for committing the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.45,0:10:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wouldn't have stolen the katana.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.84,0:10:26.73,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,0)}Matsue Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.67,0:10:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt that this is Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.42,0:10:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And judging from the times of the people before\Nand after him, I don't think he lied about when he came.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.51,0:10:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't gain anything from that, did we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.22,0:10:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, we've already considered this possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.93,0:10:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means only one person could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.18,0:10:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry and get back to the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.35,0:10:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.44,0:10:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll catch up with you soon, so you can go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.94,0:10:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, but make it quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:00.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something about this is bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.21,0:11:02.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}These times are too good to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.00,0:11:08.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.12,0:11:12.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's an extra row that's not on yesterday's page.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.04,0:11:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, could I borrow your eraser for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.17,0:11:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to write this perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.59,0:11:20.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That might have been possible with a pencil but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.80,0:11:22.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.14,0:11:24.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, could it be that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.68,0:11:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, could I also borrow your eraser for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.31,0:11:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran... Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.98,0:11:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a minute, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is still in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.90,0:11:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That brat again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.94,0:11:40.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.07,0:11:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.20,0:11:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Yamane.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.78,0:11:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.45,0:11:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.16,0:11:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishitobi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} couldn't have committed the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.92,0:11:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.25,0:11:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a car accident just outside of Izumo...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.59,0:11:58.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which occurred at 1:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.46,0:12:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was shortly before\NWanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered in Inome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.80,0:12:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to a witness testimony, the\Ndriver who committed the hit-and-run...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.89,0:12:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is currently being held on DUI charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.27,0:12:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That driver was Ishitobi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.31,0:12:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.61,0:12:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.98,0:12:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why he was frightened a couple\Ndays ago wasn't because he killed Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.61,0:12:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because he didn't want us to find\Nout he'd been driving under the influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.32,0:12:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if that's true, who is our culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.28,0:12:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's neither Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} nor Ezumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.95,0:12:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has a valid alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:35.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the likelihood that Ishitobi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could\Nhave committed the crime is next to nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.13,0:12:39.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, all of the suspects are innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.00,0:12:40.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.05,0:12:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.72,0:12:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.64,0:12:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't progress in the investigation at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.26,0:12:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.53,0:13:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the manager, Fujie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.86,0:13:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Mouri. I need to meet with you as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.37,0:13:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll leave the time and place we meet up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll let you know why when you get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.58,0:13:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.21,0:13:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Fujie. I have something I need to discuss with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.96,0:13:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want to discuss something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.05,0:13:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm waiting for you in front of Hinomisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.06,0:13:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is a wonderful lighthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:38.96,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Hinomisaki
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.56,0:13:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's 43.65 meters, and is said to be the tallest in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.07,0:13:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure is a pretty lighthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.99,0:13:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was built in the 36th year of the Meiji era,\Nwhich corresponds to 1903 on the Gregorian calendar...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.66,0:13:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was built over 100 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.79,0:13:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,100 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.00,0:13:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we were told to wait at Hinomisaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.83,0:14:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.34,0:14:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lighthouse is already closed for the night,\Nbut I'm pretty sure there's a viewing platform in front of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.84,0:14:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.88,0:14:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could he want to discuss with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.52,0:14:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting, Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.35,0:14:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.19,0:14:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You're the one who called me here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please find me a good match...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.11,0:14:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's here! The Sleeping Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.20,0:14:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just like the rumors said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.62,0:14:43.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I recall you describing\NWanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as a serpent earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.96,0:14:47.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Crocodile Snake\NHis name is "Wani", but he seems more like a "hebi".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.09,0:14:50.22,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's a monster that's always meddling in other\Npeople's business and appropriating whatever he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.22,0:14:52.72,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Indeed, he's just like an evil serpent!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.01,0:14:58.68,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: According to legend, the serpent demanded that the people of\NIzumo sacrifice one of their daughters to it every year for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.01,0:14:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it may be true that Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} forced others to\Ngive him what he wanted, like the Eight-Headed Serpent...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.27,0:15:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's no reason to kill him, Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.57,0:15:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.40,0:15:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That again, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.99,0:15:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.82,0:15:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you also confirm his alibi at Matsue Castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.95,0:15:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a well-planned trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.37,0:15:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.25,0:15:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You started thinking about killing Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwhen you visited Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} several days ago, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.26,0:15:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You intimated Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.97,0:15:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the hopes she would marry Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and\Nprevent him from taking over your marriage ceremony hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.35,0:15:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But such a selfish wish had no chance to be granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.19,0:15:46.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, in your desperation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.15,0:15:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found something that was forgotten at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.58,0:15:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's when you got an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.75,0:16:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two days ago, you made a couple phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One was to Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was something along the lines of...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.01,0:16:12.42,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll show you the best way to win Mezumi Eiko{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} over!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.43,0:16:15.26,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It would be best to talk in a place away from the crowds...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.26,0:16:18.72,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So, let's meet in Inome at 1:00 PM tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second call was to Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, imitating Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.69,0:16:27.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I won't to meet you tomorrow.\NPlease come to Hinomi at 1:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.82,0:16:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't the one who called?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.49,0:16:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He imitated his voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.65,0:16:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, he said he caught a cold\Nwhich made his voice sound different than usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.79,0:16:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He arranged a half-hour time difference\Nbetween the two appointments...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.92,0:16:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he didn't want Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to see\NWanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murderer while she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.96,0:16:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, yesterday afternoon around 1:00 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.80,0:16:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You carried out your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.26,0:16:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You checked Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s watch to get the exact time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.14,0:16:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which was 1:05 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.97,0:17:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You placed the lost pendant beside the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.77,0:17:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you went to Matsue Castle by car...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.19,0:17:10.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And perfected your alibi using the name registry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.07,0:17:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for him to have signed that, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.11,0:17:18.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how fast he drove, he couldn't\Nhave arrived at Matsue Castle before 2:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.03,0:17:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because you went to\NMatsue Castle twice yesterday, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.12,0:17:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.96,0:17:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first time was in the morning, to set up the trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.95,0:18:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being the first to sign the registry for the day,\Nit was easy for you to add an extra row for the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.53,0:18:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And replace the ballpoint pen at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.50,0:18:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He replaced the ballpoint pen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.62,0:18:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He exchanged it for an identical erasable ballpoint pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.46,0:18:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After killing Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nyou went back to Matsue Castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.75,0:18:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found someone who registered at 1:05 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.73,0:18:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Erased their name, and wrote your own, making it\Nlook like you were there during Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.36,0:18:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how you built your alibi, knowing that it takes\Nan hour to get to Matsue Castle from the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.03,0:18:41.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a false alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.49,0:18:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you test it, you can easily see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That all of yesterday's names were\Nwritten with an erasable ballpoint pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.25,0:18:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think about it, it's normal to write\Nyour name, address, and the date in a registry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.34,0:18:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you don't usually write the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.26,0:19:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, no one wrote the time in until yesterday morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you were the first to register yesterday,\Neveryone who registered after you also wrote in the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.85,0:19:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone had already filled the time in, one would\Nnaturally assume they're supposed to do so as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.48,0:19:16.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wouldn't suspect anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.03,0:19:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used that psychological trick, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.36,0:19:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you have to say about that, Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.07,0:19:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the proof that I was the\Nfirst to register yesterday morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.08,0:19:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name "Yamada Ichiro" is indeed a credible false name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.71,0:19:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is with the address: "Narisei City, Tokyo".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.05,0:19:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Narisei City, Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.92,0:19:38.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.05,0:19:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How does that prove I'm the one who wrote that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.84,0:19:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is Narisei City a problem, you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.05,0:19:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you lived in Tokyo\Nwhen you were a student, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.48,0:19:53.40,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wanibuchi was my kouhai at the\NTeito University of Business in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.40,0:19:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That statement settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.02,0:20:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You lived in a dormitory in Narisei\NCity during your four years as a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.32,0:20:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, but it doesn't answer my question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.41,0:20:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it possible that someone named\NYamada Ichiro living in Narisei City wrote that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.91,0:20:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.00,0:20:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Narisei City is no longer a part of Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.09,0:20:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It merged with the neighboring Haido City...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.46,0:20:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the Narisei name was dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.63,0:20:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.05,0:20:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the first you've heard about this, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.43,0:20:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.81,0:20:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Narisei City no longer exists...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.23,0:20:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the truth is that I knew I was\Ndone for from the the first moment I saw you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.87,0:20:41.13,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.74,0:20:43.86,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}T-The famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.86,0:20:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was only a matter of\Ntime until the truth was revealed...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.83,0:20:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.96,0:21:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.72,0:21:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like watching the sunset here at Hinomisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.39,0:21:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is probably the last time I'll be able to see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to meet here so it would\Nbe engraved in my eyes for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.73,0:21:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know I was being selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.19,0:21:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ezumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I didn't want\NWanibuchi to take over what's important to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.24,0:21:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to become\Nanother one of that monster's heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.49,0:21:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was my motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.45,0:21:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.12,0:21:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.04,0:21:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.75,0:21:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Protect Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.33,0:21:40.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You never know what hideous\Nmonster will rear its head next.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.51,0:21:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a beautiful sunset!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.47,0:21:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where were you this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.81,0:21:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, those two look like they're getting along well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.39,0:21:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sure do!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.02,0:22:01.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The knot of love must have\Nfinally brought their love to fruition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.66,0:23:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We aren't going back to Tokyo until this thing sticks!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.29,0:23:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll definitely get it this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.75,0:23:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.75,0:23:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.25,0:23:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.84,0:23:47.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.04,0:23:49.44,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\b1}Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.49,0:23:50.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.59,0:23:53.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Isn't it wrong to mess up other people's love lives?
